						<summary>

						<p>On a stone kept in the Travellers Bungalow.</p>						

						<p>Anantavarmadēva.</p>						

						<p>Dated year 11, <hi rend="italic">uttarāyaṇa-Sankrānti</hi> (Written in Telugu-Kannaḍa characters of 11th-12th century A.D.)</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of the village under his enjoyment <hi rend="italic">(bhukti)</hi> to god Gōkarṇēśvaradēva of Guḍivāḍa by Jeddama-nāyaka for food-offerings of the deity.</p>						

